a.xlink:title: Render the envmap as a textured cube. This method does nothing if the envmap is not a skybox.
Bind the texture to enable its use in a shader.
Get the pointer on the active camera data.
Update the OpenGL state of the envmap : texture, skybox and shaders if needed.
Generate the OpenGL representation of the texture according to the stored TextureData.
Update (i.e. send to GPU) the buffers marked as dirty.
